## Before / After Reference Examples

### Blog paragraph — before
> Sydecar's platform is a testament to the transformative power of technology in today's evolving private markets landscape. It's not just about launching SPVs — it's about empowering fund managers to focus on what truly matters: building relationships and delivering returns. Our robust, comprehensive solution seamlessly handles the back office so you don't have to.

### Blog paragraph — after
> Sydecar automates the back office work that takes up most of a fund manager's week: banking setup, compliance filings, investor onboarding, and tax reporting. The platform handles these so GPs can spend time on deals and investor relationships rather than paperwork.

**Changes:** Removed "testament to the transformative power", "evolving landscape", "robust", "comprehensive", "seamlessly", contrastive framing ("not just X — it's Y"), contraction ("don't"), and em dash. Rewrote to name specific features and outcomes.

---

### CEO email opener — before
> We are pleased to announce that Sydecar has achieved significant milestones this year, and we are excited about the opportunities that lie ahead as we continue our journey toward becoming the leading platform in private markets.

### CEO email opener — after
> Last year, Sydecar processed more than 760 SPVs. That is the number I keep coming back to — not because it is big, but because of what it tells us about how much the market has changed.

**Changes:** Removed "pleased to announce", "significant milestones", "excited about", "journey toward", and vague forward-looking filler. Replaced with a specific number and a plain observation. Note: the em dash in the revised version should be removed — rewrite as: "That is the number I keep coming back to. Not because it is big, but because of what it tells us about how much the market has changed."

---

### Landing page headline — before
> Unlock the Power of Seamless SPV Formation

### Landing page headline — after
> Launch an SPV in hours, not weeks.

**Changes:** Removed "unlock", "power of", "seamless". Replaced with a specific, testable claim that means something to the reader.

